==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prosthesis
<hw>Pros"the*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/ an addition, fr. <?/ to put to, to add; <?/ to + <?/ to put,
place.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The addition to the
human body of some artificial part, to replace one that is wanting, as a
log or an eye; -- called also <altname>prothesis</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>The prefixing of one or more
letters to the beginning of a word, as in <xex>be</xex>loved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prosthetic</ent>⟦br⟧
